An Act to expand virtual school eligibility for school choice students.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Chapter 370 of the Acts of 2012 is hereby amended by adding the following section:
2 Section 11
3 Notwithstanding the provisions of any general or special law to the contrary, students
4 enrolled in a school choice program, as established by section 12B of chapter 76 of the
5 Massachusetts General Laws, may enroll in a virtual school operated by the accepting school
6 district.
